@node Creating a Component
@section Creating a Component

Three types of component can be defined in Dezyne:

@itemize

@item     The first type is a component that has only a name defined and has no implementation.  In Dezyne this is
        a placeholder for a component that is implemented in another programming language.

@item     The second type is a component that has an implementation marked by the ‘behaviour’ keyword.

@item     The third type is a component decomposed into others that has an implementation marked by the @code{system} keyword.  The system specifies contained component instances, see further
@ref{Decomposing a Component},.
@end itemize

@menu
* Component Syntax::
* Importing Models::
* Ports::
* External::
* Injected::
* Behaviour::
@end menu

@node Component Syntax
@subsection Component Syntax

A component definition is named, and introduces a list of provides and
requires interfaces and optionally behaviour or a system.

@subsubheading 1) regular component with behaviour

@example
@b{component} component_name
@{
  @b{provides} iprotocol p; // list of provided interfaces
  @b{requires} iused r;     // list of required interfaces
  @b{behaviour}             // the component's behaviour
  @{ ...  @}
@}
@end example

@subsubheading 2) foreign component: placeholder for component implemented in another programming language

@example
@b{component} component_name
@{
  @b{provides} iprotocol p; // list of provided interfaces
  @b{requires} iused r;     // list of required interfaces
@}
@end example

@subsubheading 3) system component
@example
@b{component} component_name
@{
  @b{provides} iprotocol p; // list of provided interfaces
  @b{requires} iused r;     // list of required interfaces
  @b{system}                // the component's system composition
  @{ ...  @}
@}
@end example

@subsubsection Examples

@subsubsection A Simple Leaf Component

The following component implements one interface and a straightforward
behaviour section.

@example
@b{component} leaf
@{
  @b{provides} icontrol control;
  @b{requires} isensor sensor;
  @b{behaviour}
  @{
    @b{on} control.event(): @{ @}
  @}
@}
@end example

@subsubsection A Foreign Component

This component has no implementation in Dezyne.  It represents a
component implemented in another programming language.

@example
@b{component} foreign_leaf
@{
  @b{requires} isensor sensor;
@}
@end example

@subsubsection A System Component

A component decomposed into two components where these components are
connected via their ports.

@example
@b{component} composition
@{
  provides icontrol control;
  @b{system}
  @{
    leaf l;
    foreign_leaf f;
    control <=> l.control;
    l.sensor <=> f.sensor;
  @}
@}
@end example

