@node Importing Models
@subsection Importing Models

When a component refers to other components or interfaces and their
details, the definition of these has to be known.

An import clause is available to load the definition from separate
files holding interface or component definitions.

@subsubsection Syntax

The keyword @b{import} is used to import interface or component
definition files.

@example
@b{import} file-name.dzn;
@b{import} lib/another-name.dzn;
@end example

Each import clause will search the import path on the file system for a
file with the required name, and include the content.

@subsubsection Examples

@subsubsection A component importing an interface

The component @code{leaf} implements the @code{icontrol} interface for
which the definition is imported using @code{import}.

@example
@b{import} icontrol.dzn
@b{component} leaf
@{
  @b{provides} icontrol control;
  @b{behaviour}
  @{
    @b{on} control.event(): @{ @}
  @}
@}
@end example

