@node Ports
@subsection Ports

A port is an instance of an interface.  A component has ports to
communicate with other components.

The keyword @b{provides} is used to specify that a component provides an
implementation of an interface.

The keyword @b{requires} is used to specify that a component uses or
requires an interface.

A component must provide an implementation for all in-events of provided
and all out events of required interfaces.

@subsubsection Syntax

@example
@b{provides} some_interface port;
@end example

@example
@b{requires} some_interface port;
@end example

@example
@b{requires} @b{external} some_interface port; // (1) (Since 2.0.0)
@end example

@example
@b{requires} @b{injected} Interface port;   // (2)
@end example

1) port to a component with possibly delaying communication channel (@pxref{External})

2) port to a shared resource (@pxref{Injected})

@subsubsection Examples

@subsubsection A component implementing one interface

The component Leaf implements the ISensor interface that has one
in-event called event.

@example
@b{component} leaf
@{
  @b{provides} icontrol control;
  @b{behaviour}
  @{
    @b{on} control.event(): @{ @}
  @}
@}
@end example

