@node Using Conditional Statements
@subsection Using Conditional Statements

Conditional statements (if-else) can be used to program decision making
on which actions to perform

@subsubsection Syntax

The keyword @code{if} is used for a simple conditional statement:

@example
if (expression) statement-true;
@end example

In this case when the expression is true then statement-true will be executed.

An if-else construction can be used for programming more elaborate
decisions.

@example
if (expression) statement-true;
else statement-false;
@end example

if the expression is true then statement-true will be executed, else
statement-true is skipped and statement-false is executed.

