@node Restrictions Multiple Provides
@subsection Restrictions Multiple Provides

For a component with a behaviour and with multiple provides ports, two
restrictions hold.  These restrictions relate to the fact that activity
cannot be forked.  These are the restrictions:

@table @code
@item V-fork
Within the handling of an in-event of a provides port, it is not allowed
to post an out-event on another provides port.

@item Y-fork
Within the handling of an out-event of a requires port, it is not
allowed to post an out-event to more than one provides port.

The violation of any of these restrictions will be reported as a
compliance error.
@end table

