@node Well-formedness
@chapter Well-formedness
The syntax as defined in @ref{Dezyne Syntax} defines an asd language
which is not restrictive enough for practical use.  This page describes
a collection of well-formedness checks that are defined on top of the
syntax.  Some of these checks are "common sense", other ones are needed
to define appropriate semantics.

