@section Checks
Well-formedness checks on the Behaviour part of a model come in a number
of categories:

@itemize

@item Directional: @i{triggers} and @i{actions} are expected at different places.

@item Nesting: the imperative part of the language (@code{assign}s, @code{action}s,
function @code{call}s) are only allowed in the 'leaves' of the language
constructs.

@item Mixing: The mix of statements within a @code{compound}s is restricted.

@item Guards: There are some restrictions on what is allowed in a Guard.

@item Functions: a function body should be imperative, and have a well-defined return.

@end itemize
@i{Note: a trigger is an event prefixed by 'on' in the behaviour, an
action is an event inside the body of a trigger.}

Well-formedness checks for a composite Component are:

@itemize

@item Binding: all ports should be bound correctly.

@end itemize

