@section Well-formedness Checks -- Reply

A 'reply' is required in the handling of a valued (i.e.  non-void) event.
It is also required in case an event (that might be void) is used in
'blocking' mode; in that case the occurrence of the reply might be
postponed.  In general this is hard to check statically.  What can be
checked is described below.

@anchor{Reply not allowed on 'requires' port}
@subsection Reply not allowed on 'requires' port

A 'reply' which is issued to release a blocking event refers to the
event's port.  Since blocking is effective on 'provides' ports only, a
well-formedness error is issued when a 'requires' port name is used.  An
